# Chun Ya (Spring Bud) Green Tea
https://www.teavivre.com/organic-chun-ya-green-tea.html

Summary
Origin: 	
Mt. Tiangong (天宫山), Juexi Town, Yibin City, Sichuan Province, China

Harvest Time: 	
April 12, 2022

Plucking Standard:
One bud with one or two leaves

Dry leaf: 	
Tightly curled tea leaves, blackish green color with white hairs

Aroma:  	
A delicious mixed aroma of bean and flower

Liquor:  	
Bright yellowish green

Taste:  	
Refreshing and sweet taste; thick texture and long-lasting bean aroma

Tea Bush: 	
Ming Xuan 131 Tea

Tea Garden: 	
Mt. Tiangong Tea Garden (about 900m to 1350m above sea level)

Caffeine: 	
Low caffeine (less than 10% of a cup of coffee)

Storage: 	
Store in airtight, opaque packaging; keep refrigerated

Shelf Life: 	
18 Months

Recommend Brewing Method
Cup Method
		
Chinese Gongfu Method
Teacup: 8.8oz / 250ml 		
185℉ / 85℃ 		
3g Tea 	
Brewing time: 3 - 5 mins